Here's how to implement this in your `EditProductPage`:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/gesture back):**

```csharp
protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        ShowConfirmationDialog();
        return true; // cancel navigation
    }
    return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
}

private async void ShowConfirmationDialog()
{
    bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
        "Unsaved Changes",
        "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
        "Discard", "Stay");

    if (leave)
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**2. Custom "Cancel" back button (replaces Shell's back arrow):**

```csharp
Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
{
    Text = "Cancel",
    Command = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
            ShowConfirmationDialog();
        else
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    })
});
```

You can set this in the constructor or in XAML:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior Text="Cancel">
        <BackButtonBehavior.Command>
            <x:Static Member="local:EditProductPage.BackCommand"/>
        </BackButtonBehavior.Command>
    </BackButtonBehavior>
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` handles Android back button/swipe; returning `true` cancels navigation.
- `BackButtonBehavior` replaces the Shell toolbar back button (iOS/Android top-left).
- Both paths should funnel through the same confirmation logic.
